    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-08-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-08-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="507"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d507">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Taylor</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-08-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1897</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 750.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose copy of the memorial of Gustav Salomon
                    &amp; Bros., of New York City, who complain that they are the owners of some
                    1,645 bales of tobacco purchased by their agent in the provinces of Pinar del
                    Rio and Havana, Cuba, prior to the publication of the prohibitory edict of
                    General Weyler, and that the said tobacco, being ready for shipment and proved
                    to have been purchased, as above alleged, prior to the edict of General Weyler,
                    is being detained (permission to export the same being denied by the Spanish
                    authorities), to their great loss and damage.</p>
                <p>You will bring the case to the attention of the Spanish Government and endeavor
                    to obtain permission for the exportation of the tobacco in question.</p>
                <p>Respectfully, yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Sherman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
